  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In September, the Germans suddenly announced that every Pole has to have an identity card.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the way to get at this, you submit your birth certificate and you fill out a form and then you come and pick up the identity card from the police.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I did what every other Pole did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I submitted my birth certificate, I filled out the form, and I came and I picked up my identity card.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was one of the very few Jews, because later I met many Jews, including my brother, who lived on these Aryan papers, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But they had all forged papers, which looked very closely to the-- they were good forgeries, you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "However, if their papers would have been checked in the police for [? authenticity, ?] they would have failed at that check.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Mine, at least I knew that it's like a legitimate document, that it will pass.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Still, though, I was in one danger.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If they asked me to drop my pants, which they did-- as times went on, it became very popular to ask people just on the mere suspicion, even if they were not Jews, drop your pants.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or sometimes they would even didn't take them to the side of the street, drop your pants.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would observe if the person was showing that he scared or hesitant and wouldn't drop his pants immediately, right there he was suspect, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that became a big issue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And really, it became a big problem.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in May of 1943, I managed-- we managed to find a surgeon who was willing to operate and make the penis look as though it was not circumcised.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
